OL,6,FThe rules state that "due impartiality
OL,7,Fmust be preserved on matters of major
OL,8,Fpolitical and industrial controversy"
OL,9,Fand there should be "an appropriately
OL,10,Fwide range of significant views"
OL,11,Fincluded.
OL,13,FThe channel previously lost a High
OL,14,FCourt challenge to temporarily block
OL,15,FOfcom from sanctioning it, with GB
OL,16,FNews' lawyers arguing that it would
OL,17,Fcause "irreparable damage" to its
OL,18,Freputation.
