OL,6,FIn October, Mr Justice Chamberlain
OL,7,Fsaid that the "likely impact" on the
OL,8,Fchannel had been "overstated", but
OL,9,Fgave them the go-ahead to challenge
OL,10,Fthe finding that it had breached
OL,11,FOfcom's rules in the High Court.
OL,13,FEarlier this year, the channel was put
OL,14,F"on notice" that more breaches of due
OL,15,Fimpartiality rules "may result in the
OL,16,Fimposition of a statutory sanction",
OL,17,Ffollowing then-sitting MPs, and a
OL,18,FConservative minister being found to
OL,19,Fhave broken rules on politicians
OL,20,F"acting as newsreaders".
