OL,6,F"The High Court has already granted GB
OL,7,FNews permission to bring a judicial
OL,8,Freview to challenge Ofcom's decision
OL,9,Fthat the programme was in breach of
OL,10,Fdue impartiality requirements.
OL,12,F"The sanction proposed by Ofcom is
OL,13,Ftherefore still subject to that legal
OL,14,Fchallenge.
OL,16,F"The plan to sanction GB News flies in
OL,17,Fthe face of Ofcom's duty to act
OL,18,Ffairly, lawfully and proportionately
OL,19,Fto safeguard free speech, particularly
OL,20,Fpolitical speech and on matters of
OL,21,Fpublic interest."
